0it%2C%20you%20realize%20that%20it%20means%20you're%20working%20more%20hours%20than%20you're%20not%2C%20six%20days%20a%20week%2C%20sometimes%20seven.%20It's%20consistent%2013-hour%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20him%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Blong%20shift%26quot%3B%20isn't%20just%20a%20late%20night%20here%20or%20there.%20It's%20months%20of%20overnight%20rotations.%20It's%20waking%20up%20at%204%3A30%20a.m.%20on%20a%20Saturday%20and%20not%20getting%20home%20until%209%20p.m.%20on%20some%20days.%20It's%20missing%20holidays%2C%20birthdays%2C%20and%20weekends.%20It's%20walking%20through%20the%20door%2C%20emotionally%20drained%20after%20performing%20chest%20compressions%20for%2036%20minutes%2C%20or%20losing%20a%20patient%20you%20fought%20for%20all%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f3bb5f4b-2809-4b00-a7b1-eedc104d9239%5C%22%3EResidency%20is%20all-consuming%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20partner%2C%20I've%20had%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20live%20alongside%20someone%20dealing%20with%20these%20things.%20That%20hasn't%20always%20been%20easy.%20I'm%20not%20someone%20who%20naturally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkeys-success-long-happy-51-year-marriage-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethrives%20on%20independence%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20I've%20always%20loved%20the%20closeness%20that%20comes%20with%20partnership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20finding%20myself%20navigating%20life%20more%20solo%20than%20expected%2C%20managing%20plans%2C%20meals%2C%20chores%2C%20and%20my%20own%20emotional%20highs%20and%20lows%2C%20has%20been%20a%20real%20adjustment.%20I'm%20not%20just%20sitting%20around%20waiting%20for%20him%20to%20walk%20through%20the%20door%2C%20but%20I'd%20be%20lying%20if%20I%20said%20I%20didn't%20miss%20having%20him%20there%20more%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7698827-9b20-4c6f-b4ed-346175888476%5C%22%3EWhat%20makes%20it%20harder%20is%20that%20there's%20no%20true%20guidance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20don't%20fully%20understand%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20married%20to%20someone%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20medical%20training.%20His%20schedule%20isn't%20his%20own.%20We%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-struggling-plan-family-trip-teens-busy-lives-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan't%20easily%20plan%20vacations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20can't%20always%20promise%20he'll%20make%20it%20to%20dinner.%20And%20when%20something%20small%2C%20like%20taking%20out%20the%20trash%2C%20gets%20overlooked%2C%20I%20have%20to%20remind%20myself%20that%20this%20is%20someone%20who%20just%20worked%2014%20hours%20trying%20to%20save%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20typical%20relationship%2C%20you%20divide%20and%20conquer.%20But%20I've%20learned%20that%20in%20for%20us%20right%20now%2C%20support%20looks%20a%20little%20different.%20It's%20picking%20up%20the%20slack%20without%20keeping%20score%2C%20and%20it's%20knowing%20that%20love%2C%20right%20now%2C%20doesn't%20always%20mean%20time%20together.%20Instead%2C%20it%20means%20empathy%2C%20patience%2C%20and%20staying%20tethered%20even%20when%20life%20pulls%20hard%20in%20another%20direction.%20It%20means%20listening%20to%20and%20consoling%20each%20other%20when%20we've%20had%20a%20tough%20day%2C%20even%20when%20the%20definition%20of%20%26quot%3Btough%26quot%3B%20looks%20drastically%20different%20in%20each%20of%20our%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20first%20started%20living%20together%20when%20he%20was%20in%20medical%20school%2C%20and%20we%20had%20set%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsplit-household-chores-based-on-strengths-interests-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etasks%20around%20the%20house%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20taking%20the%20trash%20out%20and%20cleaning%20the%20toilets%2C%20and%20I%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20vacuuming%20and%20laundry.%20Whoever%20cooked%20dinner%2C%20the%20other%20person%20cleaned%20up.%20We%20grocery%20shopped%20together.%20The%20last%20person%20out%20of%20bed%20had%20to%20make%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20in%20this%20phase%20of%20life%2C%20these%20tasks%20fall%20mostly%20on%20me.%20Sure%2C%20it%20took%20an%20adjustment%20period%20of%20getting%20used%20to%2C%20but%20I've%20learned%20that%20a%20strong%20relationship%20is%20less%20about%20keeping%20track%20of%20who's%20doing%20what%20and%20more%20about%20how%20you%20can%20support%20and%20love%20your%20partner.%20And%20when%20he%20has%20the%20time%20to%20help%2C%20he%20absolutely%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228db8291f-8661-4175-9f2d-62d8276cbb30%5C%22%3EI%20don't%20compare%20my%20relationship%20with%20others%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20plenty%20of%20Reddit%20threads%20sharing%20stories%20like%20mine%2C%20but%20I%20try%20not%20to%20read%20them.%20Every%20relationship%20is%20different%2C%20even%20within%20the%20medical%20world%2C%20and%20if%20I%20compare%20our%20relationship%20to%20others%2C%20there%20won't%20be%20any%20winners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20matters%20most%20is%20how%20we%20show%20up%20for%20each%20other%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20absolutely%20do.%20Sometimes%20that's%20him%20staying%20up%20an%20extra%2020%20minutes%20after%20a%20grueling%20overnight%20shift%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdining-out-with-kids-hard-fosters-connection-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeat%20breakfast%20with%20me%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that%20small%20moment%20means%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoving%20someone%20in%20residency%20means%20loving%20someone%20who's%20being%20stretched%20to%20their%20absolute%20limits%20and%20choosing%20not%20to%20let%20that%20stretch%20tear%20you%20apart.%20It's%20definitely%20not%20easy.%20But%20for%20us%2C%20it's%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarried-surgeon-work-redefined-support-relationships-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A17541291620