0loads%20at%2050%20cents%20per%20pound.%20At%2082%2C%20he%20now%20oversees%20operations%20%E2%80%94%20processing%20orders%2C%20arranging%20shipments%2C%20and%20calling%20clients.%20It%20beats%20watching%20TV%20all%20day%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leonard%20Carter%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688d2d743d5881a51c1e7fb9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELeonard%20Carter%2C%2082%2C%20has%20no%20intention%20of%20retiring.%3Cp%3ELeonard%20Carter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECarter%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiming-retirement-older-americans-delay-if-possible-recession-economic-uncertainty-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworks%20about%2020%20hours%20a%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20he%20has%20enough%20to%20live%20comfortably%20well%20past%20100%2C%20as%20he%20has%20a%20high-six-figure%20IRA%20and%20gets%20%242%2C500%20monthly%20from%20Social%20Security.%20Still%2C%20between%20multiple%20marriages%2C%20rising%20costs%2C%20and%20some%20tougher%20years%20with%20the%20business%2C%20finances%20haven't%20always%20been%20secure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20goes%20on%20work%20trips%20to%20the%20Midwest%2C%20and%20he%20stays%20active%20in%20his%20community%2C%20attending%20Rotary%20Club%20meetings%20and%20volunteering%20at%20historic%20sites%20nearby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20tell%20people%20I'm%20coming%20out%20of%20this%20office%20feet%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20Carter%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20sense%20of%20purpose%2C%20and%20it's%20also%20a%20sense%20of%20knowing%20I'm%20doing%20something%20good%2C%20which%20is%20recycling%20stuff%20that%20would%20go%20to%20landfills.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22135187f0-dc2f-4e45-816b-6d4155d883ee%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20odd%20jobs%20for%20the%20fun%20of%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20data%20analysis%20of%20people%2080%20and%20older%20by%20United%20For%20ALICE%2C%20part%20of%20United%20Way%20of%20Northern%20New%20Jersey%2C%20calculated%20that%20of%20the%20nearly%20550%2C000%20workers%2080%20and%20older%2C%20about%2073%25%20are%20above%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-typical-alice-middle-class-poverty-housing-food-benefits-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EALICE%20threshold%2C%20the%20minimum%20income%20needed%20to%20afford%20basic%20living%20expenses%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20suggests%20that%20most%20workers%20in%20this%20demographic%20are%20not%20desperate%20for%20additional%20income%2C%20though%20thousands%20still%20work%20to%20supplement%20their%20Social%20Security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephanie%20Hoopes%2C%20national%20director%20of%20United%20For%20ALICE%2C%20said%20that%20many%20seniors%20may%20take%20on%20part-time%20work%20for%20a%20little%20extra%20boost%20of%20financial%20security.%20And%20employers%20may%20need%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20where%20they're%20struggling%20to%20get%20workers%2C%20such%20as%20in%20the%20retail%20and%20service%20space%2C%20and%20they%20may%20be%20quite%20interested%20in%20hiring%20seniors%20because%20they're%20maybe%20more%20dependable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Kasun%2C%2086%2C%20has%20had%20a%20long%20and%20winding%20career.%20While%20working%20in%20engineering%2C%20he%20started%20selling%20archery%20equipment%20out%20of%20his%20basement.%20He%20hired%20six%20part-time%20workers%20and%20kept%20his%20full-time%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKasun%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Pennsylvania%2C%20also%20wrote%20for%20an%20outdoor%20magazine%20and%20worked%20for%20a%20railroad%20rehabilitation%20company.%20While%20working%2C%20he%20invested%20all%20his%20extra%20money%20and%20spent%20frugally%2C%20splurging%20every%20once%20in%20a%20while%20on%20items%20like%20an%20ATV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20money%20is%20like%20having%2