ine%20at%20the%20hospital%20in%20fictional%20San%20DiFrangeles%2C%20asks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20showing%20perfectly%20healthy%20people%20every%20harmless%20imperfection%20in%20their%20body%20just%20to%20scare%20them%20into%20taking%20invasive%20and%20often%20pointless%20tests%20is%20an%20unholy%20sin%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Perry%20Cox%20responds%2C%20echoing%20a%20sentiment%20many%20real%20doctors%20have%20toward%20high-end%20preventive%20scans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kelso%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688a8a2af748d8c055f696e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%20TV%20show%20Scrubs%2C%20Dr.%20Kelso%20(above)%20wants%20to%20start%20offering%20full-body%20scans%20to%20patients.%20His%20colleague%20Dr.%20Cox%20(not%20pictured)%20thinks%20that's%20a%20terrible%20idea.%3Cp%3EMitch%20Haaseth%2FDisney%20General%20Entertainment%20Content%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20more%20than%2020%20years%20since%20that%20Scrubs%20episode%20first%20aired%2C%20and%20yet%20real%20doctors%20are%20no%20closer%20to%20settling%20their%20big%20debate%20about%20full-body%20MRIs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreventive%20full-body%20MRIs%20are%20now%20used%20in%20high-end%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsimple-lifestyle-changes-longevity-doctor-lose-50-pounds-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elongevity%20clinics%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20are%20available%20through%20a%20growing%20suite%20of%20direct-to-consumer%20offerings.%20Prices%20range%20from%20%242%2C500%20or%20more%20for%20a%20one-hour%20scan%20to%20new%20AI-assisted%20offerings%20that%20cost%20%24500%20and%20only%20take%20about%2020%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224505%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kim%20k%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688a9662f748d8c055f697c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223003%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKim%20Kardashian%20promoted%20Prenuvo's%20scans%20on%20Instagram%20in%202023%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Blifesaving%20machine.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EErnesto%20Ruscio%2FGC%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStars%20and%20longevity%20fiends%2C%20including%20Kim%20Kardashian%2C%20tout%20these%20scans%20on%20social%20media%2C%20and%20everyday%20patients%20share%20real%20success%20stories%2C%20gripping%20testimonials%20of%20lifesaving%20insights%20they've%20gleaned%20from%20scanning%20their%20entire%20bodies%20for%20signs%20of%20danger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenetic%20sequencing%20pioneer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-longevity-clinic-executive-physical-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECraig%20Venter%3C%2Fa%3E%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20diagnosed%20his%20own%20prostate%20cancer%20%26quot%3Bthat%20was%20about%20to%20metastasize%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20high-end%20MRI%20%26quot%3Bafter%20being%20told%20by%20the%20best%20medical%20system%20that%20I%20didn't%20have%20prostate%20cancer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFull-body%20MRIs%20can%20detect%20cancer%20early.%20But%20they%20can%20also%20have%20you%20parting%20with%20thousands%20of%20dollars%2C%20scheduling%20numerous%20follow%20up%20appointments%20to%20chase%20little%20dots%20on%20your%20scans%2C%20and%20in%20the%20end%20revealing%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2238c87aaa-075d-445e-8d19-09205e9d11db%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20full-body%20MRI%20is%20like%20a%20security%20camera%20for%20your%20innards%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20promise%20of%20a%20full-body%20MRI%20is%20that%20it%20can%20uncover%20dangerous%20things%20happening%20inside%20you%20that%20aren't%20bad%20enough%20%E2%80%94%20yet%20%E2%80%94%20to%20get%20picked%20up%20on%20other%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanielle%20Hoeg%20is%20a%20perfect%20example%20of%20how%20this%20can%20work.%20A%20non-smoker%20in%20her%20early%2040s%20and%20mom%20of%20three%2C%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider%20she%20decided%20to%20do%20a%20Prenuvo%20scan%20after%20some%20%26quot%3Bwonky%26quot%3B%20blood%20work%20was%20taken%20at%20her%20doctor's%20office%2C%20which%20suggested%20something%20might%20be%20wrong.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20signed%20up%20for%20a%20%242%2C500%20Prenuvo%20scan%20(not%20covered%20by%20insurance)%2C%20which%20took%20about%20an%20hour.%20The%20scan%20highlighted%20a%20few%20things%3A%20some%20moderate%20spinal%20degeneration%20and%20a%20lingering%20sinus%20infection.%20It%20also%20flagged%20a%20%26quot%3Bminor%26quot%3B%20white%20cloud%20on%20her%20lung%2C%20an%20%26quot%3Bindeterminate%20lesion%26quot%3B%20that%20%26quot%3Bappears%20at%20low%20risk%20of%20becoming%20problematic%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20Prenuvo%20report%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20blood%20test%20for%20lung%20cancer%20came%20back%20negative%2C%20but%20a%20CT%20scan%20her%20doctor%20ordered%20showed%20that%2C%20sure%20enough%2C%20that%20lung%20spot%20was%20likely%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecancer.%20She%20eventually%20had%20a%20stage%201%20tumor%20removed%2C%20just%20three%20months%20after%20her%20Prenuvo%20scan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoeg%20was%20in%20shock.%20She%20was%20a%2043-year-old%2C%20healthy%20non-smoker%20with%20lung%20cancer.%20How%20could%20this%20be%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20out%20there%20smoking%2C%20asking%20for%20lung%20cancer%2C%20I'm%20not%20working%20in%20a%20coal%20mine%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20she%20caught%20this%20cancer%20early%2C%20she%20didn't%20have%20to%20undergo%20any%20aggressive%20radiation%20or%20chemotherapy%20treatments.%20She%20tells%20everyone%20she%20can%20about%20her%20experience%20with%20Prenuvo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20little%20bit%20less%20lung%2C%20I%20have%20some%20scars%2C%20but%20I'm%20OK%2C%20and%20I'm%20here%2C%20and%20I'm%20with%20my%20kids%2C%20and%20swimming%20and%20running%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmi%20Gal%2C%20founder%20of%20Prenuvo%20competitor%20Ezra%2C%20recently%20acquired%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffunction-health-500-dollar-blood-test-i-tried-it-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFunction%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20says%20this%20is%20exactly%20what%20full-body%20scans%20are%20meant%20for.%20They're%20helping%20find%20cancer%20that%20either%20can't%20be%20screened%20for%20or%20won't%20get%20picked%20up%20on%20regular%20screening%20tests%20because%20it's%20not%20big%20enough%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20mother%20passed%20away%20from%20cancer%20because%20she%20found%20cancer%20late%2C%26quot%3B%20Gal%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BI've%20dedicated%20my%20career%20and%20my%20life%20really%20to%20helping%20everyone%20in%20the%20world%20detect%20cancer%20early.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222043%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22emi%20gal%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688a95563d5881a51c1e4fee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222043%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEzra%20founder%20Emi%20Gal.%3Cp%3EEzra%2FFunction%20Health%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scans%20can%20also%20pick%20up%20back%20and%20spine%20problems%2C%20aneurysms%2C%20liver%20disease%2C%20and%20cysts.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInevitably%2C%20they%20will%20also%20flag%20many%20things%20as%20worrisome%20that%20people%20don't%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20at%20all%2C%20like%20benign%20scar%20tissue%20or%20inflammation%20lingering%20from%20a%20recent%20illness%20or%20injury.%20The%20scan%20can't%20tell%20you%20definitively%2C%20%26quot%3Bhey%2C%20this%20is%20trouble.%26quot%3B%20It%20just%20shows%20you%20when%20something's%20there.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb5d53ef-992f-4976-bade-66e3b6782a99%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20ultrasounds%20the%20real%20untapped%20medical%20tool%20of%20the%20future%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222340%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22full%20body%20scan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688a893cf748d8c055f696d8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224221%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhat%20is%20in%20there%3F%20Everything.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20fictional%20Dr.%20Cox%20presciently%20said%20on%20Scrubs%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20get%20this%20scan%2C%20the%20next%20year%20of%20your%20life%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20series%20of%20endless%20tests.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrenuvo%20says%20that%20nearly%20half%20of%20its%20patients%20%26quot%3Bfind%20something%20to%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20doctors%20want%20to%20know%3A%20Are%20they%20saving%20lives%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20you%20won't%20find%20major%20medical%20boards%20or%20cancer%20advocacy%20organizations%20recommending%20full-body%20MRIs.%20There%20isn't%20the%20hard%20evidence%20they'd%20need%20to%20back%20up%20a%20medical%20recommendation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20end%20goal%20is%20saving%20years%20of%20life%2C%20helping%20people%20live%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Samir%20Abboud%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20emergency%20radiology%20at%20Northwestern%20Memorial%20Hospital%20in%20Chicago%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20annual%20scans%20are%20overkill%2C%20our%20annual%20check-ups%20are%20often%20not%20enough.%20Independent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F30699470%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereviews%3C%2Fa%3E%20consistently%20show%20that%20yearly%20health%20checks%20have%20little%20to%20no%20effect%20on%20preventing%20deadly%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Tim%20Arling%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20concierge%20medicine%20practice%20focused%20on%20longevity%2C%20says%20he%20only%20occasionally%20recommends%20full-body%20MRIs%20to%20his%20patients.%20What%20he's%20started%20doing%20more%20often%20is%20spending%20a%20few%20extra%20minutes%20waving%20a%20little%20medical%20wand%20over%20parts%20of%20a%20patient's%20body%20as%20a%20preliminary%20scan%20for%20trouble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20using%20a%20portable%20ultrasound%20machine%2C%20the%20same%20device%20doctors%20use%20to%20look%20at%20a%20fetus%20as%20it's%20developing%20in%20utero.%20The%20technique%20is%20common%20in%20Japan%2C%20where%20doctors%20often%20glide%20ultrasound%20wands%20over%20a%20person's%20thyroid%2C%20as%20an%20initial%20screen%20for%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20technician%20performs%20an%20ultrasound%20on%20an%20Achilles%20tendon.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6572397658e7c0c29a2ad2fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221663%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20technician%20performs%20an%20ultrasound%20on%20an%20Achilles%20tendon.%3Cp%3EPyrosky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20thyroid%20gland%2C%20Arling%20sometimes%20glides%20his%20ultrasound%20over%20a%20patient's%20liver%2C%20kidneys%2C%20or%20aorta%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20a%20little%20extension%20of%20the%20physical%20exam.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20see%20something%2C%20I'll%20have%20a%20discussion%20with%20the%20patient%2C%20we'll%20decide%20if%20we%20want%20to%20do%20something%20in%20real%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20costs%20nothing%20extra%20to%20the%20patient%20and%20takes%20just%20a%20few%20extra%20minutes.%20Critically%2C%20it%20also%20includes%20the%20doctor%20in%20the%20discussion%20from%20the%20get-go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoeg's%20stage%201%20cancer%20was%20graded%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bminor%26quot%3B%20finding%20by%20Prenuvo.%20If%20Abboud%2C%20who's%20both%20a%20doctor%20and%20a%20friend%2C%20hadn't%20said%20she%20should%20get%20it%20looked%20at%20ASAP%2C%20would%20she%20have%20known%20to%20take%20the%20finding%20so%20seriously%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22691%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22prenuvo%20scan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688ccb16f748d8c055f6b6ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22765%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHoeg%20shared%20this%20image%20of%20her%20lung.%20The%20%26quot%3Bminor%26quot%3B%20finding%20ended%20up%20being%20stage%201%20lung%20cancer.%3Cp%3Ecourtesy%20of%20Danielle%20Hoeg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EArling%20said%20he%20went%20through%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20bizarre%20three-week%20period%26quot%3B%20last%20year%20where%20he%20ended%20up%20flagging%20a%20case%20of%20early-stage%20liver%20cancer%2C%20plus%20another%20case%20of%20early-stage%20kidney%20cancer%20using%20ultrasounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20primary%20care%20is%20trying%20to%20catch%20things%20earlier%2C%20the%20question%20comes%20down%20to%20how%20can%20we%20do%20it%20in%20a%20way%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20add%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20extra%20cost%20or%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20extra%20waste%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20%26quot%3Bwe%20can%20start%20just%20sort%20of%20waving%20wands%20over%20people%20and%20getting%20a%20little%20more%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2279df3b51-b620-4fa2-afde-508f29593ec4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20decide%20if%20you%20should%20get%20a%20full-body%20scan%3A%205%20questions%20to%20ask%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MRI%20radiologists%20or%20technologists%20working%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64999c95c218ba0019a80ea8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMRI%20machines%20currently%20depend%20on%20liquid%20helium%20coolant%20to%20keep%20cool%20enough%20to%20operate.%3Cp%3Esimonkr%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20people%2C%20doctors%20are%20already%20in%20agreement%20that%20full-body%20cancer%20scans%20are%20a%20good%20thing.%20If%20you%20have%20a%20rare%20condition%20called%20Li-Fraumeni%20syndrome%2C%20which%20puts%20you%20at%20greater%20risk%20of%20developing%20all%20sorts%20of%20cancer%2C%20annual%20full-body%20scans%20are%20a%20go-to%2C%20and%20they're%20covered%20by%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20everybody%20else%2C%20the%20jury%20%E2%80%94%20a%20jury%20full%20of%20practicing%20physicians%20%E2%80%94%20is%20still%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20interested%20in%20a%20full-body%20scan%2C%20Dr.%20Arling%20recommends%20weighing%20a%20few%20key%20factors%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b6d34964-1328-42dc-9666-aad830c2d467%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20What's%20your%20family%20history%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20want%20to%20consider%20a%20full-body%20MRI%20if%20you've%20got%20a%20family%20history%20of%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20scan%20should%20be%20in%20addition%20to%20other%20recommended%20cancer%20screenings%20you're%20already%20doing%2C%20Arling%20said%3A%20%26quot%3Bpaps%2C%20mammos%2C%20PSAs%2C%20colonoscopies%2C%20the%20standard%20stuff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20option%20is%20a%20cancer%20blood%20test%20like%20Galleri.%20It%20costs%20%24950.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e34e4224-c369-4359-9f19-69c95a56ad4d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20What's%20your%20medical%20anxiety%20level%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20anxious%20about%20medical%20care%20or%20testing%2C%20full-body%20scans%20may%20not%20be%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20already%20have%20that%20health-anxious%20person%2C%20I'm%20not%20super%20enthusiastic%20about%20recommending%20this%20test%2C%20because%20they're%20going%20to%20find%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Arling%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221969c79e-a034-4830-8c99-5b6ef088b3b5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20What's%20your%20level%20of%20concern%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20full-body%20scans%20are%20good%20at%20%26quot%3Blooking%20for%20trouble%2C%26quot%3B%20Arling%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20really%20trying%20to%20find%20the%20thing%2C%20not%20rule%20out%20the%20thing%2C%20then%20the%20MRI%20is%20going%20to%20have%20better%20data.%20It%20has%20higher%20sensitivity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt'll%20be%20more%20sensitive%20than%20a%20Galleri%20test%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2291ca986f-23ad-4c2a-b5e1-eac643445854%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20What's%20your%20budget%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20this%20the%20best%20use%20of%20a%20few%20hundred%20to%20a%20few%20thousand%20bucks%20of%20your%20cash%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMight%20you%20derive%20more%20health%20benefits%20from%20putting%20those%20dollars%20into%20things%20we%20know%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-improve-longevity-supplements-vs-exercise-and-diet-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eimprove%20healthy%20aging%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvest-day-exercise-boost-longevity-aging-expert-physiologist-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexercise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-an-exercise-routine-that-actually-works-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epersonal%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20better%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthy-eating-tips-food-routines-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enutrition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20less%20stress%20(a%20nice%20vacation%2C%20perhaps%3F)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it%20gets%20people%20being%20healthy%2C%20great%2C%20but%20if%20it's%20just%20a%20thing%20that%20rich%20people%20do%20to%20flaunt%20that%20they're%20healthier%20than%20you%2C%20it%20doesn't%20quite%20achieve%20the%20goal%2C%26quot%3B%20Arling%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220cb1d464-0b3a-4aa2-8c7b-3d8cda87f9a5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Is