quot%3B%20Melissa%20Swift%2C%20who%20worked%20at%20Deloitte%20and%20Korn%20Ferry%20and%20now%20runs%20a%20workplace%20consultancy%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20not%20all%20RTOs%20are%20created%20equal%2C%20and%20the%20experts%20agreed%20that%20there's%20a%20common%20mistake%20that%20makes%20RTO%20worse%3A%20unequal%20enforcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20worse%20than%20feeling%20like%20your%20coworkers%20are%20better%20treated%20without%20any%20reason%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20Roulet%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20organisational%20sociology%20and%20leadership%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BEquity%20issues%20do%20negatively%20affect%20motivation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESwagatam%20Basu%2C%20a%20senior%20director%20of%20research%20in%20Gartner's%20HR%20practice%2C%20said%20inconsistent%20mandates%20can%20create%20%26quot%3Bcompliance%20without%20commitment.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%202024%20survey%20of%206%2C466%20employees%20and%20managers%20in%2014%20countries%2C%20Gartner%20found%20that%20RTO%20mandates%20made%20employees%2010%25%20less%20likely%20to%20stay%20and%20increased%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20%26quot%3Bquiet%20quitting%26quot%3B%20by%2019%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20experts%20also%20agreed%20that%20RTO%20doesn't%20%3Cem%3Ehave%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20have%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20your%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20to%20RTO%20the%20right%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b1ce0da-4344-42ef-82bd-5f2ca34ccaea%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EData%2C%20dialogue%2C%20and%20gradual%20change%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20the%20management%20experts%20BI%20spoke%20to%20said%20RTO%20policies%20work%20best%20when%20they%20are%20flexible%20and%20give%20managers%20a%20say.%20They%20also%20offered%20some%20key%20pieces%20of%20advice%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGo%20about%20it%20gradually%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3ERoulet%20said%20five-day%20RTO%20mandates%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20companies%20should%20use%20%26quot%3Bmore%20progressive%20shifts%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20moving%20from%20two%20to%20three%20days%2C%20in%20order%20to%20help%20people%20get%20used%20to%20the%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20employees%20want%20to%20come%20in%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3ESwift%20said%20leaders%20should%20%26quot%3Bunderstand%20the%20rhythm%20of%20people's%20working%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20lest%20they%20order%20people%20%26quot%3Binto%20situations%20where%20they%20cannot%20get%20their%20work%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20noise%20of%20open-plan%20offices%20and%20phone%20calls%20can%20cause%20issues.%20Dell%20offered%20employees%20noise-defending%20headphones%20after%20they%20complained%20RTO%20had%20made%20the%20workplace%20too%20noisy%2C%20a%20source%20previously%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%223%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupport%20and%20train%20managers%20to%20guide%20the%20way%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20RTO%20mandates%20are%20designed%20by%20senior%20leadership%2C%20but%20Basu%20said%20managers%20underneath%20them%20are%20%26quot%3Bkey.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20equipped%20to%20lead%20through%20RTO%2C%20they%20can%20build%20flexible%20work%20models%20that%20preserve%20trust%20and%20performance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ideal%20is%20not%20hybrid%20or%20fully%20remote%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cooper.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20when%20a%20line%20manager%20negotiates%20with%20each%20team%20member%20what%20works%20for%20them%20and%20for%20the%20business.%20That%20gets%20higher%20productivity%2C%20better%20job%20satisfaction%2C%20and%20fewer%20sick%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-rto-without-sparking