ate%20Champion%2C%20promotes%20organic%20farming%20and%20empowers%20women%20in%20Bhitarkanika.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20persistence%20paid%20off.%20Sabita%20saved%20enough%20to%20lease%20two%20acres%20of%20land%2C%20where%20she%20now%20grows%20rice%20and%20vegetables.%20Her%20husband%20eventually%20returned%20to%20join%20her.%20With%20encouragement%20from%20her%20mother-in-law%2C%20she%20resumed%20her%20education%2C%20finished%20school%2C%20and%20now%20plans%20to%20go%20to%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20at%2026%2C%20Sabita%20is%20a%20farmer%2C%20a%20student%2C%20a%20mother%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20Climate%20Champion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20want%20to%20help%20others%20turn%20their%20lives%20around%20like%20I%20did%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Sabita%20now%20teaches%20villagers%20how%20to%20make%20organic%20fertilisers%20and%20natural%20pesticides%20using%20cow%20dung%2C%20neem%20leaves%2C%20and%20other%20plants%20%E2%80%94%20a%20skill%20that%E2%80%99s%20earned%20her%20the%20nickname%20%E2%80%98Organic%20Didi%E2%80%99.%20When%20cyclone%20Dana%20hit%2C%20she%20was%20on%20the%20frontlines%20of%20rescue%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20love%20our%20village.%20We%E2%80%99re%20so%20connected%20to%20this%20place%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20air%20is%20clean%2C%20the%20greenery%20is%20beautiful%2C%20and%20we%20live%20right%20next%20to%20the%20river%20%E2%80%94%20we%20see%20crocodiles%20all%20the%20time.%20We%E2%80%99re%20not%20scared%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20laughs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20her%20biggest%20worry%20is%20water.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20used%20to%20rain%20so%20much%20more.%20Now%20it%20comes%20late%2C%20or%20not%20at%20all.%20I%20want%20to%20grow%20two%20crops%20a%20year%2C%20but%20there%20just%20isn%E2%80%99t%20enough%20water.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5